<subSubSection id="05D699CFFF3CB3B344D1F9DFCD620C2A" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4D73CA44FF3CB3B344D1F9DFC9C00DB6" blockId="160.[151,1437,1558,1799]" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis id="7FB81656FF3CB3B344D1F9DFC9170D03" bold="true" box="[151,273,1558,1583]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace with only 3 large lateral spines, numerous minute spinules along rostrum, frontal margin of carapace. First antennae with feathery setae, second sparsely setose. Eyestalk slender, cylindrical. First pereopods chelate, pereopods 2–4 with sickle-shaped dactyls. Abdominal somites widely separated laterally, telson rounded. Carapace length to 
<quantity id="8A3467A1FF3CB3B34536F94BC9C70DB6" box="[368,449,1666,1690]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D73CA44FF3CB3B34481F96FC9FC0D92" blockId="160.[151,1437,1558,1799]" box="[199,506,1702,1727]" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">
